C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-hospital-wait-times-are-bad-physician-shortage-low-pay-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewithout%20enough%20doctors%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20go%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20type%20%26quot%3BMatch%20Day%26quot%3B%20into%20TikTok%2C%20you'll%20be%20flooded%20with%20clips%20of%20anxious%20young%20med%20students%20in%20school%20auditoriums%20ripping%20open%20letters%20to%20find%20out%20which%20residency%20they%20landed.%20It's%20a%20nerve-racking%20process%2C%20made%20even%20more%20daunting%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20everyone%20gets%20their%20results%20at%20the%20same%20time%20%E2%80%94%20together.%20Through%20the%20National%20Resident%20Matching%20Program%2C%20med%20students%20are%20interviewed%20by%20representatives%20from%20residency%20programs%2C%20and%20both%20parties%20rank%20each%20other.%20On%20Match%20Day%2C%20based%20on%20those%20rankings%2C%20the%20students%20learn%20whether%20they%20got%20into%20their%20preferred%20specialty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20being%20in%20an%20honors%20society%2C%20volunteering%2C%20joining%20clubs%2C%20and%20studying%20day%20and%20night%2C%20Match%20Day%20didn't%20go%20as%20Dr.%20Erica%20Ginsburg%20had%20hoped.%20Ginsburg%2C%2027%2C%20did%20not%20get%20matched%20with%20her%20top%20choice%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshould-you-wash-your-face-in-the-shower-dermatologists-advise-2019-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edermatology%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20specialty%20so%20competitive%20that%20about%2020%25%20of%20applicants%20don't%20match.%20%26quot%3BSome%20people%20were%20screaming%2C%20crying%20tears%20of%20joy.%20Me%20and%20my%20friend%20were%20crying%20tears%20of%20sadness%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20As%20a%20child%2C%20a%20dermatologist%20treated%20her%20for%20eczema%2C%20and%20the%20results%20gave%20her%20confidence.%20She%20wanted%20to%20do%20the%20same%20for%20others.%20Once%20she%20got%20older%2C%20she%20said%2C%20she%20realized%20that%20dermatology%20also%20%26quot%3Bhas%20it%20good%26quot%3B%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20work-life%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20want%20to%20have%20both%2C%20you%20know%2C%20a%20career%20and%20a%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20students%20compete%20for%20spots%20in%20fields%20like%20dermatology%20and%20surgery%2C%20primary%20care%20programs%20go%20unfilled.%20After%202024's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nrmp.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FAdvance-Data-Tables-2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMatch%20Day%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20were%20over%20600%20unfilled%20spots%20in%20family%20medicine%2C%20nearly%20500%20in%20internal%20medicine%2C%20and%20250%20in%20pediatrics.%20Meanwhile%2C%20about%206.3%25%20of%20applicants%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%201%2C200%20med%20students%20%E2%80%94%20were%20left%20unmatched.%20(About%20900%20of%20them%20found%20positions%20through%20a%20subsequent%20matching%20program%20for%20unmatched%20students%2C%20but%20that%20still%20left%20hundreds%20of%20future%20doctors%20without%20a%20residency%20spot%20and%20164%20unfilled%20primary%20care%20positions%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20surprising%20that%20so%20many%20people%20want%20to%20avoid%20primary%20care.%20When%20third-year%20med%20students%20rotate%20through%20underresourced%20primary%20care%20practices%2C%20they%20witness%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoctors-chief-medical-officers-healthcare-google-uber-salesforce-executives-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20stressed%20out%20doctors%20are%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Even%20those%20who%20may%20have%20wanted%20to%20go%20into%20the%20field%20sometimes%20change%20their%20minds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20been%20in%20situations%20where%20they're%20saying%2C%20'OK%2C%20here's%20a%20new%20patient.%20You've%20got%20seven%20minutes%20to%20try%20to%20get%20an%20intake%20on%20who%20they%20are%2C%20write%20their%20notes%2C'%26quot%3B%20says%20Annelise%20Silva%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20American%20Medical%20Student%20Association%2C%20who%20recently%20graduated%20from%20the%20Boonshoft%20School%20of%20Medicine%20at%20Wright%20State%20University.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20family%20practice%20clinicians%20who%20see%20upwards%20of%2020%20to%2030%20patients%20a%20day.%26quot%3B%20They%20often%20spend%20hours%20after%20their%20appointments%20writing%20up%20clinic%20notes%2C%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Yalda%20Jabbarpour%2C%20a%20family%20doctor%20and%20director%20of%20the%20Robert%20Graham%20Center%20at%20the%20American%20Academy%20of%20Family%20Physicians%2C%20says%20primary%20care%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bbackbone%26quot%3B%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-hospitals-bankrupt-closing-wealthy-investors-looting-reselling-private-equity-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eour%20healthcare%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20the%20US%20allocated%20only%20%240.05%20in%202021%20to%20the%20field%20for%20every%20dollar%20spent%20on%20healthcare.%20%26quot%3BMost%20countries%20that%20have%20a%20robust%20primary%20care%20system%20and%20better%20health%20outcomes%2C%20longer%20life%20expectancy%2C%20are%20closer%20to%20double%20or%20even%20triple%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20She%20and%20other%20researchers%20found%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.commonwealthfund.org%2Fpublications%2Fissue-briefs%2F2024%2Fmar%2Ffinger-on-pulse-primary-care-us-nine-countries%23%3A~%3Atext%3DInvest%2520in%2520primary%2520care%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewealthy%20countries%3C%2Fa%3E%20spent%20an%20average%20of%20%240.14%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20undervaluing%20of%20primary%20care%20is%20structural.%20Most%20doctors%20are%20paid%20through%20the%20fee-for-service%20structure%20%E2%80%94%20a%20monetary%20value%20is%20assigned%20to%20each%20service%20based%20on%20the%20risk%20and%20complexity%20involved.%20%26quot%3BThat%20system%20is%20pretty%20biased%20against%20cognitive%20specialties%20and%20towards%20procedural%20specialties%2C%26quot%3B%20Jabbarpour%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20specialties%20where%20you're%20taking%20time%20to%20talk%20to%20the%20patient%2C%20coordinate%20their%20care%2C%20think%20about%20their%20complex%20medical%20issues%2C%20but%20aren't%20necessarily%20doing%20a%20procedure%20on%20them%2C%20are%20going%20to%20be%20paid%20less%2C%20and%20that%20is%20primary%20care.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20%26quot%3Btiny%20violins%20come%20out%20when%20we're%20talking%20about%20salaries%20of%20physicians%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BYes%2C%20a%20cardiologist%20makes%20more%20than%20a%20primary%20care%20physician.%20A%20primary%20care%20physician%20still%20makes%20a%20pretty%20good%20salary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202023%20Medscape%20report%20said%20family%20doctors%20made%20an%20average%20of%20%24255%2C000%20in%202022.%20That's%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20the%20%24619%2C000%20average%20salary%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhighest-paying-jobs-for-doctors-2016-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehighest-paid%20doctors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20plastic%20surgeons.%20When%20you've%20accumulated%20over%20%24200%2C000%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-gave-up-doctor-dream-despite-looming-debt-worth-it-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edebt%20to%20go%20to%20medical%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20pull%20toward%20a%20better%20salary%20is%20tough%20to%20ignore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBias%20against%20primary%20care%2C%20like%20what%20Anna%20experienced%20at%20Georgetown%2C%20can%20also%20deter%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpecialty%20disrespect%20was%20defined%20by%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC7205122%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%26quot%3Bunwarranted%2C%20negative%2C%20denigrating%2C%20even%20sarcastic%20comments%20made%20by%20trainees%20and%20physicians%20about%20different%20specialties.%26quot%3B%20It%20surveyed%20med%20students%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Washington%20School%20of%20Medicine%20between%202008%20and%202012%2C%20and%2087.7%25%20of%20students%20who%20matched%20into%20family%20medicine%20residencies%20said%20they%20had%20experienced%20specialty%20disrespect%20%E2%80%94%20a%20higher%20percentage%20than%20for%20any%20other%20specialty%20%E2%80%94%20compared%20with%20just%20under%2080%25%20of%20all%20respondents.%20About%20one-quarter%20of%20respondents%20said%20the%20comments%20had%20a%20moderate%20to%20strong%20impact%20on%20their%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20among%20students%20who%20wind%20up%20in%20primary%20care%2C%20a%20good%20chunk%20of%20them%20don't%20stay%20there.%20In%202021%2C%2037%25%20of%20all%20residents%20started%20out%20training%20in%20primary%20care%2C%20but%20after%20three%20to%20five%20years%2C%20only%2021%25%20remained%20practicing%20it%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.milbank.org%2Fpublications%2Fthe-health-of-us-primary-care-2024-scorecard-report-no-one-can-see-you-now%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%25202021%252C%252037%2525%2520of%2520all%2Csubspecialized%2520or%2520became%2520hospitalists%2520instead.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPrimary%20Care%20Scorecard%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%20Instead%2C%20many%20go%20on%20to%20subspecialize%20in%20fields%20like%20endocrinology%20or%20rheumatology%20or%20work%20in%20hospitals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20doctors%20most%20people%20meet%20are%20in%20primary%20care.%20When%20there%20aren't%20enough%20primary%20care%20doctors%2C%20diseases%20aren't%20caught%20early%20and%20patients%20have%20a%20harder%20time%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchronic-illness-resume-helped-me-get-better-healthcare-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanaging%20chronic%20diseases%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Already%2C%20nearly%20one%20in%20every%20three%20Americans%20lacks%20reliable%20access%20to%20primary%20care%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nachc.org%2Fnachc-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F01%2FPolicyPapers_Workforce_FINAL_Jan2025.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Association%20of%20Community%20Health%20Centers%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20in%20a%20data%20analysis.%20Researchers%20from%20Case%20Western%20Reserve%20University%20and%20Academia%20Sinica%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC9881650%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestimate%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20number%20of%20people%20over%2050%20with%20at%20least%20one%20chronic%20illness%20will%20double%20from%2071.5%20million%20in%202020%20to%20142.6%20million%20by%202050%2C%20which%20would%20add%20pressure%20to%20an%20already%20stressed%20healthcare%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20impact%20will%20be%20felt%20most%20acutely%20by%20those%20in%20rural%20communities%20and%20people%20of%20color%20%E2%80%94%20a%20problem%20that%20could%20get%20worse%20if%20the%20Trump%20administration%20cuts%20healthcare%20spending.%20The%20House%20of%20Representatives%20passed%20a%20budget%20on%20February%2025%20that%20would%20cut%20%24880%20billion%20from%20the%20House%20Energy%20and%20Commerce%20Committee%2C%20which%20includes%20Medicaid%2C%20though%20it%20hasn't%20yet%20been%20passed%20into%20law.%20Some%20medical%20students%20interested%20in%20maternal%20health%20are%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffuture-doctors-residency-states-where-abortion-legal-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eavoiding%20states%20with%20abortion%20bans%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20practicing%20OB-GYNs%20in%20those%20places%20are%20fleeing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPatients%20don't%20have%20access%20to%20healthcare.%20It's%20really%20hard%20for%20them%20to%20get%20in%20to%20see%20their%20primary%20care%20doctor.%20Because%20of%20that%2C%20we%20have%20higher%20rates%20of%20chronic%20disease.%20We%20have%20higher%20mental%20health%20burden.%20We%20have%20lower%20vaccination%20rates%20than%20we've%20ever%20had%2C%26quot%3B%20Jabbarpour%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Amol%20Navathe%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20health%20policy%2C%20medicine%2C%20and%20healthcare%20management%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%2C%20says%20the%20shortage%20is%20also%20moving%20patients%20away%20from%20more%20holistic%20relationships%20with%20a%20doctor%20familiar%20with%20their%20needs%20and%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-giving-up-medical-care-cant-afford-costs-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20fragmented%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20patients%20go%20to%20urgent%20care%20or%20seek%20out%20specialists%20on%20their%20own.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20good%20for%20patient%20health%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20good%20for%20the%20efficiency%20of%20how%20our%20resources%20get%20used.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20address%20some%20of%20these%20issues%2C%20Jabbarpour%20says%2C%20the%20US%20needs%20to%20invest%20in%20payment%20models%20that%20value%20primary%20care%20more%20effectively.%20Some%20medical%20systems%20are%20already%20trying%20this.%20Navathe%20has%20worked%20with%20the%20Hawaii%20Medical%20Service%20Association%2C%20a%20licensee%20of%20the%20Blue%20Cross%20Blue%20Shield%20Association%2C%20to%20design%20a%20system%20through%20which%20physicians%20are%20paid%20a%20fixed%20rate%20per%20patient%20and%20then%20given%20additional%20fees%20for%20services%20like%20providing%20vaccines%20or%20dermatology.%20The%20goals%20are%20to%20help%20patients%20get%20better%20care%20and%20reduce%20the%20number%20of%20patients%20doctors%20need%20to%20see%20to%20get%20paid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20structure%2C%20which%20started%20as%20a%20pilot%20project%20in%202016%20and%20is%20now%20in%20place%20across%20the%20state%2C%20has%20had%20some%20success%3A%20More%20people%20got%20vaccines%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmedical-tourists-health-screenings-tests-exams-on-vacation-mexico-turkey-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecancer%20screenings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20there%20were%20fewer%20emergency%20room%20visits%20and%20hospitalizations%20for%20chronic%20diseases.%20Navathe%20says%20Medicare%20has%20tested%20similar%20pilot%20projects%20but%20would%20require%20approval%20from%20Congress%20to%20roll%20them%20out%20widely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMedicare%20funding%20for%20graduate%20medical%20schools%20is%20another%20bottleneck.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20these%20large%20academic%20hospitals%2C%20which%20aren't%20necessarily%20primary-care-oriented%2C%26quot%3B%20Jabbarpour%20says.%20%26quot%3BMost%20people%20are%20not%20going%20to%20the%20hospital%20to%20get%20their%20healthcare.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20schools%20are%20trying%20to%20address%20the%20shortage%3A%20Ginsburg%20says%20her%20medical%20school%20at%20Florida%20State%20University%20enthusiastically%20promoted%20going%20into%20primary%20care%20%E2%80%94%20resulting%20in%20nearly%20half%20of%20her%20class%20matching%20into%20the%20field.%20She%20was%20one%20of%20only%20three%20who%20went%20into%20dermatology.%20%26quot%3BWe%20had%20all%20these%20people%20who%20just%20really%20love%20medicine%20for%20underserved%20populations%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BSo%20we%20had%20all%20these%20clubs%2C%20organizations%20that%20were%20really%20geared%20towards%20primary%20care.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20other%20schools%2C%20addressing%20the%20issue%20of%20specialty%20disrespect%20head-on%20can%20make%20a%20difference.%20Georgetown's%20School%20of%20Medicine%20has%20launched%20a%20campaign%20to%20combat%20the%20issue%2C%20with%20posters%20around%20the%20school%20featuring%20common%20negative%20tropes%20about%20various%20specialties%20and%20rebuttals%20to%20these%20comments.%20In%20a%202020%20survey%20of%20Georgetown%20med%20students%2C%2031%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20derogatory%20comments%20affected%20their%20career%20decisions%2C%20and%2038%25%20said%20they%20had%20disparaged%20a%20specialty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnna%20says%20she%20understands%20the%20instinct%20more%20experienced%20doctors%20have%20in%20wanting%20to%20protect%20students%20from%20negative%20experiences.%20%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20naive%20to%20the%20realities%20of%20their%20specialties%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20But%20she%20wishes%20these%20topics%20were%20brought%20up%20in%20a%20more%20neutral%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20people%20come%20into%20medical%20school%20with%20an%20inherent%20drive%20to%20help%20people%20and%20to%20want%20to%20do%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20hear%20these%20comments%2C%20it%20pulls%20you%20further%20from%20your%20values%20and%20doesn't%20allow%20you%20to%20explore%20and%20feel%20good%20about%20what%20you%20want%20to%20go%20into.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20generation%20of%20doctors%20has%20a%20lot%20riding%20on%20them.%20The%20last%20thing%20the%20medical%20system%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20government%20%E2%80%94%20should%20be%20doing%20is%20deterring%20them%20from%20their%20job%3A%20keeping%20Americans%20healthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fmanisha-krishnan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EManisha%20Krishnan%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20an%20Emmy%20award-winning%20journalist%20who%20covers%20healthcare.%20She%20is%20based%20in%20Brooklyn.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-doctor-shortage-med-students-primary-care-family-medicine-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742458921000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67cb323eb8b41a9673fa04d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%