https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftariff-business-uncertainty-ceo-trump-mexico-canada-china-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etariffs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20launched%20her%20Tennessee%20whiskey%20brand%2C%20Uncle%20Nearest%2C%20in%202017%2C%20right%20before%20the%20European%20Union%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-european-union-targeting-bourbon-jeans-motorcycles-2018-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslapped%20tariffs%20on%20American%20whiskeys%20and%20bourbons%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20part%20of%20a%20back-and-forth%20trade%20war%20with%20Donald%20Trump%20in%202018.%20That%20means%20Weaver's%20international%20sales%20strategy%20has%20been%20affected%2C%20basically%2C%20since%20%26quot%3Bday%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20And%20because%20Uncle%20Nearest%20was%20a%20new%20kid%20on%20the%20block%2C%20the%20company%20didn't%20really%20have%20much%20wiggle%20room%20on%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20couldn't%20pass%20on%20those%20tariffs%20to%20the%20consumer%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe%20had%20to%20absorb%20them%2C%20and%20there%20was%20absolutely%20no%20way%20we%20could%20absorb%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Europe%20suspended%20whiskey%20tariffs%20in%202021%2C%20Weaver%20wasn't%20home-free%2C%20either.%20She%20knew%20the%20suspension%20might%20not%20be%20permanent%2C%20especially%20if%20Trump%20landed%20back%20in%20the%20White%20House.%20So%20when%20he%20won%20in%20November%2C%20Uncle%20Nearest%20pulled%20international%20sales%20from%20their%20annual%20earnings%20forecast%20in%20anticipation%20of%20a%20return%20to%20the%20trade%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20to%20make%20a%20decision%20to%20not%20focus%20as%20much%20on%20international%20until%20the%20trade%20war%20was%20over%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20it's%20not%20been%20over.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20return%20the%20trade%20war%20has%3A%20The%20EU%20is%20threatening%20to%20implement%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-trade-war-stirring-booze-battles-eu-us-wine-whiskey-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E50%25%20tariff%20on%20American%20whiskeys%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20now%2C%20there's%20a%20new%20and%20surprising%20trade%20foe%3A%20Canada.%20The%20United%20States'%20neighbors%20to%20the%20north%20aren't%20putting%20tariffs%20on%20US-made%20bourbon%20in%20response%20to%20Trump's%20various%20economic%20threats%3B%20they're%20simply%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-pub-owner-protest-boycott-plan-stop-using-us-products-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emaking%20it%20impossible%20to%20buy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20pulled%20us%20off%20the%20shelf%20right%20along%20with%20Jack%20Daniels%2C%26quot%3B%20Weaver%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reignition%20of%20the%20international%20brown%20liquor%20battle%20is%20another%20headache%20for%20an%20industry%20already%20reeling.%20After%20multiple%20years%20of%20solid%20growth%20in%20the%202010s%20and%20a%20pandemic-driven%20boom%20in%202020%2C%20domestic%20US%20whiskey%20sales%20have%20been%20on%20the%20decline%2C%20while%20international%20sales%20have%20flattened.%20Data%20from%20IWSR%2C%20an%20analytics%20firm%20focused%20on%20the%20alcohol%20industry%2C%20found%20that%20sales%20volume%20of%20US%20whiskeys%20fell%20by%201.2%25%20in%202023%2C%20and%20another%202%25%20in%202024.%20Globally%2C%20sales%20were%20flat%20in%202023%20and%20are%20on%20track%20to%20decline%20in%202024.%20(American%20whiskeys%20include%20bourbon%2C%20Tennessee%2C%20and%20rye.%20The%20distinctions%20are%20key%20since%20all%20bourbons%20are%20whiskeys%2C%20but%20not%20all%20whiskeys%20are%20bourbon.%20If%20it's%20American%20or%20Irish%2C%20it's%20whiskey%2C%20with%20the%20%26quot%3Be.%26quot%3B%20If%20it's%20from%20Scotland%2C%20England%2C%20Japan%2C%20or%20most%20other%20places%2C%20it's%20spelled%20whisky.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20customers%2C%20this%20could%20mean%20some%20of%20their%20favorite%20craft%20brands%20might%20struggle%20and%20even%20fold%20if%20they%20can't%20get%20on%20enough%20shelves%20in%20America%20or%20abroad.%20Ironically%2C%20though%2C%20the%20bourbon%20industry's%20tariff-related%20headaches%20may%20wind%20up%20being%20a%20plus%20for%20American%20drinkers%20in%20the%20near%20term%20%E2%80%94%20distilleries%20could%20wind%20up%20with%20a%20ton%20of%20inventory%20they%20can't%20sell%20overseas%20and%20push%20more%20volumes%20and%20varieties%20onto%20the%20US%20market.%20That%20could%20mean%20prices%20on%20American%20booze%20come%20down%20in%20the%20near%20term%2C%20though%20some%20analysts%20say%20distributors%20could%20just%20charge%20more%20on%20everything%2C%20wherever%20it's%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20denying%20the%20industry%20is%20facing%20troubles%2C%20but%20Weaver%20chafes%20at%20the%20idea%20of%20calling%20what's%20happening%20a%20bourbon%20%26quot%3Bbust.%26quot%3B%20Uncle%20Nearest%20is%20growing%20as%20a%20brand%2C%20and%20there%20are%20still%20plenty%20of%20whiskey%20drinkers%20out%20there%2C%20at%20home%20and%20abroad.%20Instead%2C%20what's%20happening%20is%20more%20of%20a%20normalization%2C%20and%20one%20she%20thinks%20more%20people%20should%20have%20seen%20coming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEveryone%20was%20so%20caught%20up%20in%20this%20'boom%2C'%20no%20one%20was%20forecasting%20for%20the%20correction%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Whatever%20the%20case%2C%20Trump's%20latest%20moves%20are%20a%20sobering%20moment%20for%20an%20industry%20that%20can%20no%20longer%20deny%20its%20growing%20pains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20modern%20whiskey%20trend%20in%20America%20dates%20back%20to%20the%20%26quot%3BMad%20Men%26quot%3B%20era%20of%20the%201950s%20and%20'60s%2C%20explained%20Marten%20Lodewijks%2C%20the%20president%20of%20IWSR%20US.%20It's%20popularity%20started%20tapering%20off%20in%20the%20'70s%20%E2%80%94%20people%20tend%20not%20to%20want%20to%20drink%20what%20their%20parents%20drank.%20In%20the%20'80s%20and%20'90s%2C%20whiskey%20really%20struggled%2C%20which%20was%20a%20curse%20and%20a%20blessing%2C%20because%20it%20got%20to%20sit%20and%20age%20until%20it%20picked%20up%20in%20popularity%20once%20again%20in%20the%202000s%2C%20around%20when%20the%20show%20%26quot%3BMad%20Men%26quot%3B%20came%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20were%20sort%20of%20the%20glory%20days%20for%20Scotch%20whisky%2C%26quot%3B%20Lodewijks%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20bourbon%20industry%20was%20a%20little%20bit%20later%20to%20the%20party%2C%20but%20obviously%20they%20weren't%20blind%20to%20what%20was%20happening.%20And%20so%20they%20rose%20with%20the%20tide%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20decade%20or%20so%2C%20bourbon%20has%20really%20taken%20off%2C%20too.%20Much%20like%20Scotch%2C%20bourbon%20makers%20have%20focused%20on%20premiumization%20%E2%80%94%20improving%20the%20quality%20and%20raising%20the%20price%20point.%20Where%20it%20was%20once%20seen%20as%20a%20product%20for%20drunks%2C%20it's%20now%20considered%20fancy.%20Because%20bourbon%20ages%20for%20less%20time%20than%20Scotch%20and%20has%20laxer%20rules%20around%20it%20in%20areas%20such%20as%20ingredients%2C%20distillers%20can%20be%20more%20dynamic%20in%20their%20approach%2C%20too.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20sort%20of%20take%20more%20chances%2C%26quot%3B%20Lodewijks%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20have%20to%20wait%2012%20years%20to%20figure%20out%20whether%20or%20not%20your%20innovation%20is%20a%20complete%20miss%20or%20a%20potential%20success.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkybourbon.com%2Findustry-news%2Fkentucky-bourbon-trail-grows-to-60-destinations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKentucky%20Distillers'%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20industry%20group%2C%20Kentucky%20produced%203.2%20million%20barrels%20of%20whiskey%20in%202024%20and%20has%20a%20record%2014.3%20million%20barrels%20aging.%20Multiple%20new%20producers%20and%20brands%20have%20popped%20up%2C%20bourbon%20collecting%20has%20risen%20in%20popularity%2C%20and%20some%20consumers%20have%20been%20willing%20and%20able%20to%20spend%20big%20on%20high-end%20bottles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20put%20these%20trends%20on%20overdrive.%20People%20were%20sitting%20at%20home%20bored%20with%20money%20to%20spend%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbooze-sales-are-booming-as-liquor-stores-are-deemed-essential-2020-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey%20were%20spending%20more%20of%20it%20on%20alcohol%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20massive%20runup%20during%20COVID%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tzvi%20Wiesel%2C%20a%20longtime%20whiskey%20investor%20and%20trader%20and%20the%20CEO%20of%20Baxus%2C%20a%20spirits%20trading%20platform.%20%26quot%3BSo%20all%20of%20these%20distilleries%20and%20investors%20and%20everyone%20got%20a%20little%20bit%20ahead%20of%20themselves%2C%20and%20they're%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20there's%20going%20to%20be%20this%20level%20of%20demand%20and%20growth%20is%20going%20to%20continue%20forever.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivate%20investors%20got%20in%20on%20the%20action%2C%20pouring%20money%20into%20distilleries%20and%20upping%20production.%20%26quot%3BThey%20built%20the%20capacity%20to%20make%20a%20million%20new%20barrels%20a%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Wiesel%20said.%20The%20problem%20was%2C%20there%20wasn't%20actually%20a%20sustainable%20place%20for%20that%20demand%20and%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20influx%20of%20money%20chasing%20the%20increased%20demand%20led%20to%20what's%20become%20a%20market%20flush%20with%20product%20that%20has%20nowhere%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20hedge%20funds%20and%20the%20private%20equity%20players%2C%20they've%20gone%20out%20and%20bought%20barrels%2C%20but%20they%20don't%20have%20a%20brand%20to%20go%20along%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Trey%20Zoeller%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20chief%20strategist%20at%20Jefferson's%20Bourbon.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20bourbon%20was%20very%20scarce%2C%20that%20might've%20been%20a%20good%20investment.%20Now%2C%20there's%20not%20nearly%20as%20many%20buyers%20for%20that%20as%20there%20were%20when%20there's%20such%20scarcity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20hopes%20for%20a%20new%20normal%2C%20bourbon%20has%20long%20been%20a%20cyclical%20industry.%20Optimists%20expected%20the%20upward%20trajectory%20kicked%20off%20by%20the%20pandemic%20to%20continue%2C%20but%20the%20market's%20come%20back%20down%20to%20earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20demand%20is%20clearly%20decelerating.%20By%202022%2C%20Americans%20had%20returned%20to%20their%20normal%20drinking%20habits%20%E2%80%94%20when%20you're%20back%20in%20the%20office%2C%20pouring%20an%20old-fashioned%20at%202%20in%20the%20afternoon%20is%20a%20real%20no-no.%20Amid%20inflation%20and%20dwindling%20pandemic-driven%20savings%2C%20there's%20also%20been%20a%20squeeze%20on%20consumers'%20wallets.%20Alcohol%20is%20a%20discretionary%20item%2C%20meaning%20it's%20a%20want%2C%20not%20a%20need%2C%20and%20when%20budgets%20are%20tight%2C%20people%20tend%20to%20lay%20off.%20There%20are%20structural%20factors%20in%20play%20as%20well.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-drinking-less-alcohol-bad-news-concert-venues-promoters-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%20is%20drinking%20less%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarijuana-infused-beverages-600-million-market-2022-2018-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECannabis%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20be%20taking%20some%20market%20share%20from%20booze.%20GLP-1s%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fozempic-curbs-alcohol-cravings-could-disrupt-addiction-treatment-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOzempic%20appear%20to%20curb%20alcohol%20cravings%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Those%20are%20%26quot%3Bprobably%20having%20an%20impact%20on%20the%20margins%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Nadine%20Sarwat%2C%20an%20analyst%20who%20covers%20the%20beverage%20and%20cannabis%20industries%20at%20Bernstein%2C%20though%20it's%20not%20clear%20they're%20huge%20factors%20%E2%80%94%20most%2024-year-olds%20(of%20any%20generation)%20are%20not%20high-end%20whiskey%20drinkers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20supply%20side%2C%20the%20decline%20in%20consumer%20interest%20is%20happening%20at%20a%20time%20when%20there's%20a%20glut%20of%20whiskey%20available.%20Because%20bourbon%20has%20to%20age%20for%20at%20least%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20%E2%80%94%20most%20are%20kept%20for%20four%20to%20six%20years%20%E2%80%94%20producers%20have%20to%20anticipate%20demand%20years%20in%20advance.%20It's%20become%20increasingly%20clear%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20producers%20overshot%20their%20estimates.%20There's%20a%20ton%20of%20bourbon%20sitting%20in%20barrels%20with%20no%20bottles%20to%20pour%20it%20into%20or%20brands%20that%20want%20to%20buy%20it.%20(Some%20brands%20distill%20their%20own%20whiskeys%3B%20some%20buy%20it%20from%20larger%20distilleries%20on%20contract%3B%20some%20do%20both%20and%20even%20blend%20different%20barrels%20together.)%20While%20distillers%20can%20sit%20on%20barrels%20for%20a%20while%2C%20there%20are%20limits%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20product.%20Most%20bourbon%20has%20about%20a%2010-year%20age%20limit%20before%20it%20turns.%20Many%20investors%20are%20on%20a%20tighter%20timeline%20ito%20get%20their%20returns%2C%20meaning%20they%20have%20to%20cut%20prices%20on%20barrels%20to%20move%20them%20on%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20I%20was%20paying%20for%20four-year-old%20Kentucky%20bourbon%20three%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20can%20now%20get%2010-year-old%20Kentucky%20bourbon%20cheaper%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Blake%20Riber%2C%20who%20runs%20the%20craft%20spirits%20platform%20Seelbach's%20and%20blogs%20about%20the%20whiskey%20industry%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fbourbonr.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBourbonr%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20just%20wild%2C%20the%20pricing%20on%20it%20and%20how%20much%20that%20has%20just%20crashed%20in%2C%20call%20it%2C%2012%20months.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20producers%20have%20started%20to%20recognize%20the%20writing%20on%20the%20wall%20and%20scaled%20back%2C%20such%20as%20the%20distilled%20spirits%20maker%20MGP%20and%20the%20alcohol%20conglomerates%20Diageo%20and%20Brown-Forman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20challenge%20that%20they're%20all%20going%20to%20be%20facing%20over%20the%20next%20few%20years%20is%2C%20what%20do%20I%20do%20with%20all%20of%20the%20extra%20liquid%20in%20order%20to%20either%20let%20it%20age%20more%20or%20are%20there%20other%20outlets%20that%20I%20can%20use%3F%26quot%3B%20Lodewijks%20said.%20That%20may%20mean%20more%20flavored%20whiskeys%20or%20more%20whiskey-based%20ready-to-drink%20cocktails%20%E2%80%94%20whatever%20gets%20it%20poured%20before%20it%20goes%20bad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tariffs%2C%20of%20course%2C%20are%20throwing%20a%20wrench%20in%20an%20already%20difficult%20situation.%20As%20part%20of%20Trump's%20trade%20war%2C%20the%20EU%20is%20mulling%20ending%20the%20suspension%20of%20its%20tariffs%20on%20American%20whiskeys%20in%20early%20April.%20And%20this%20time%2C%20the%20bloc%20could%20set%20the%20levies%20at%2050%25%2C%20double%20the%2025%25%20from%20the%20president's%20first%20term.%20Trump%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20has%20threatened%20a%20200%25%20tariff%20on%20wines%2C%20Champagnes%2C%20and%20other%20alcoholic%20products%20out%20of%20France%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20entirely%20clear%20what%20it%20would%20mean%20for%20the%20American%20bourbon%20industry%20if%20the%20EU%20tariffs%20take%20effect.%20Given%20the%20recent%20glut%20and%20change%20in%20domestic%20appetites%2C%20growing%20sales%20outside%20America%20has%20been%20a%20key%20release%20valve%20for%20producers.%20Bernstein's%20Sarwat%20estimates%20that%20tariffs%20would%20result%20in%20a%2010%25%20hit%20to%20operating%20income%20for%20Brown-Forman%2C%20which%20owns%20brands%20such%20as%20Jack%20Daniel's%20and%20Woodford%20Reserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20US%20volumes%20have%20been%20really%20sluggish%20over%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20the%20international%20market%20has%20always%20been%20a%20real%20positive%20for%20increased%20penetration%2C%20and%20so%20any%20further%20challenges%20in%20that%20market%20does%20not%20help%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELodewijks%20said%20the%20EU's%20original%2025%25%20tariff%20led%20to%20about%20a%2020%25%20decline%20in%20whiskey%20sales%20to%20Europe%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20we%20know%20what%20a%2050%25%20tariff%20would%20do.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20point%20at%20which%20more%20and%20more%20consumers%20aren't%20willing%20to%20spend%20or%20spend%20the%20money%20that%20it%20would%20take%20to%20buy%20the%20product.%20So%20I'm%20not%20saying%20necessarily%20it'll%20be%20more%20than%2040%25%2C%20but%20likely%2C%20it%20would%20be%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20broad%20point%20of%20Trump's%20trade%20war%20%E2%80%94%20with%20Europe%2C%20China%2C%20whoever%20%E2%80%94%20is%20ostensibly%20to%20encourage%20companies%20to%20make%20more%20goods%20in%20the%20US.%20But%20in%20spaces%20such%20as%20alcohol%2C%20it's%20not%20so%20simple.%20Tequila%20has%20to%20come%20from%20Mexico.%20Scotch%20is%20always%20from%20Scotland.%20American%20whiskey%20companies%20would%20love%20to%20sell%20more%20to%20people%20at%20home%2C%20but%20American%20drinkers%20are%20not%20picking%20up%20what%20they're%20putting%20down.%20If%20tariffs%20go%20into%20effect%20on%20alcohol%20products%20coming%20into%20the%20US%2C%20people%20won't%20necessarily%20switch%20over%20to%20domestically%20made%20bourbon.%20If%20you're%20predominantly%20a%20wine%20drinker%2C%20you%20may%20not%20be%20jonesing%20to%20swap%20that%20for%20Wild%20Turkey%20overnight.%20And%20for%20the%20industry%20and%20Americans%20who%20do%20drink%20brown%20liquor%2C%20the%20tit-for-tat%20battle%20may%20not%20be%20a%20win%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20time%20around%2C%20American%20bourbon%20and%20whiskey%20companies%20ate%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20tariffs%20instead%20of%20increasing%20prices.%20But%20not%20everyone%20in%20the%20space%20has%20such%20a%20luxury%2C%20especially%20the%20smaller%20guys%20who've%20already%20been%20pushed%20around%20by%20the%20bigger%20guys.%20They're%20trying%20to%20fight%20for%20shelf%20space%20wherever%20they%20can%20get%20it%20and%20are%20still%20trying%20to%20recover%20from%20the%202018%20tariff%20bout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%20the%20tariffs%2C%20everything%20fell%20off%20a%20cliff%2C%20and%20it%20has%20not%20recovered%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Becky%20Harris%2C%20the%20former%20president%20of%20the%20American%20Craft%20Spirits%20Association%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20Catoctin%20Creek%20distillery.%20%26quot%3BThe%20big%20producers%20do%20recover.%20They%20recover%20why%3F%20Because%20they%20have%20massive%20amounts%20of%20money%2C%20they%20can%20splash%20back%20into%20the%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20some%20small%20producers%20may%20go%20under%20if%20they%20cannot%20find%20a%20place%20to%20sell%20their%20products.%20Given%20the%20industry's%20competitiveness%2C%20they%20could%20also%20try%20to%20increase%20prices%2C%20though%20that%20may%20be%20tough.%20The%20bigger%20manufacturers%20and%20distributors%20have%20broad%20portfolios%20of%20products%20that%20encompass%20different%20types%20of%20alcohol%20from%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20world.%20If%20they%20see%20a%20price%20increase%20on%20imports%20to%20the%20US%20for%20one%20of%20their%20product%20lines%2C%20say%2C%20a%20European%20wine%20or%20Mexican%20tequila%2C%20they%20may%20increase%20prices%20on%20American-made%20products%2C%20too%2C%20either%20because%20they%20have%20to%20or%20just%20because%20they%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20likely%20that%20under%20the%20cover%20of%20tariffs%2C%20domestic%20products%20will%20also%20go%20up%20in%20price%2C%26quot%3B%20Lodewijks%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20analysts%20and%20industry%20professionals%20told%20me%20the%20supply%20glut%20could%20lead%20to%20producers%20dropping%20their%20prices%20in%20the%20short%20term%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20move%20their%20booze%2C%20Tom%20Fischer%2C%20who%20runs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FBourbonBlog.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBourbonBlog.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20the%20long-term%20news%20may%20not%20be%20as%20encouraging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20distilleries%20lose%20sales%20in%20Europe%20due%20to%20higher%20prices%20from%20EU%20tariffs%2C%20those%20same%20American%20distilleries%20may%20raise%20domestic%20prices%20to%20offset%20lost%20revenue%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20has%20been%20shown%20to%20happen%20in%20the%20past%20with%20other%20goods%2C%20so%20we%20hope%20that%20bourbon%20won't%20be%20the%20next%20casualty.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20trade%20war%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20hit%20the%20industry%20in%20more%20tangential%20places%2C%20too.%20Riber%20noted%20that%20not%20much%20glass%20manufacturing%20happens%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20he's%20starting%20to%20hear%20concerns%20from%20bourbon%20brands%20about%20potential%20tariffs%20on%20glass%20imports%20and%20needing%20to%20raise%20prices%20to%20make%20up%20for%20it.%20%26quot%3BAt%20some%20point%2C%20that's%20going%20to%20have%20to%20get%20passed%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Wiesel%20brought%20up%20the%20increased%20need%20for%20warehouse%20space%20as%20bourbon%20piles%20up%20that%20can't%20be%20sold.%20%26quot%3BDistilleries%20are%20going%20to%20have%20to%20invest%20a%20ton%20into%20the%20actual%20physical%20infrastructure%20to%20hold%20onto%20all%20of%20these%20barrels%20that%20they%20own%20that%20are%20maturing%20for%20longer%20because%20they%20don't%20have%20a%20place%20to%20sell%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20there's%20Canada%2C%20which%20the%20president%20has%20picked%20a%20somewhat%20confusing%20fight%20with.%20He's%20threatened%2025%25%20tariffs%20on%20imports%20from%20Canada%2C%20has%20said%20he%20wants%20to%20make%20it%20the%2051st%20state%2C%20and%20has%20taken%20an%20overall%20aggressive%20approach%20to%20the%20country.%20It's%20sparked%20a%20sense%20of%20patriotism%20in%20Canada%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20boycotts%20on%20American-made%20products%2C%20including%20bourbon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCanada%20is%20just%20pulling%20American%20products.%20They're%20essentially%20sending%20notes%20to%20their%20suppliers%20saying%2C%20'Hey%2C%20no%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20anything%20against%20you%2C%20but%20my%20customers%20are%20not%20buying%20American%20right%20now.%20They're%20angry%2C'%26quot%3B%20Harris%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20they%20said%2C%20'Even%20when%20the%20tariffs%20are%20gone%2C%20this%20is%20going%20to%20take%20a%20while%2C%20so%20don't%20hold%20your%20breath.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFischer%20expressed%20similar%20concerns%20about%20the%20potential%20European%20tariffs.%20%26quot%3BA%2050%25%20tariff%20risks%20pricing%20us%20out%20of%20key%20markets%2C%20and%20once%20those%20consumers%20shift%2C%20they%20may%20not%20come%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20just%20roll%20back%20a%20tariff%20and%20expect%20loyalty%20to%20return%20overnight.%20This%20is%20long-term%20damage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeaver%2C%20from%20Uncle%20Nearest%2C%20is%20still%20optimistic%20about%20the%20future.%20Bourbon%20is%20one%20of%20America's%20most%20important%20exports%20%26quot%3Bin%20terms%20of%20symbolism%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20and%20if%20you%20look%20at%20bourbon's%20history%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe've%20always%20had%20these%20times%20when%20people%20are%20drinking%20less%20of%20it%2C%20but%20then%20it%20comes%20roaring%20back.%26quot%3B%20She%20gets%20that%20the%20president%20is%20doing%20what%20he%20thinks%20he%20needs%20to%20do%20to%20negotiate%20trade%20agreements.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20it%20might%20be%20nice%20if%20he%20gave%20the%20industry%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20PR%20boost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20best%20thing%20he%20could%20do%20is%20literally%20say%2C%20'Hey%2C%20America%2C%20this%20is%20going%20to%20be%20in%20our%20best%20interest%2C'%20because%20this%20is%20clearly%20what%20he%20believes%2C%20'but%20while%20we're%20working%20this%20out%2C%20we%20really%20need%20you%20to%20double%20down%20on%20bourbon%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20%26quot%3BBuy%20American%26quot%3B%20can%20become%20%26quot%3BDrink%20American%2C%26quot%3B%20even%20if%20the%20president%20himself%20doesn't%20drink.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbourbon-whiskey-tariffs-europe-canada-trump-trade-war-prices-cost-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742458441000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67db1fba69253ccddf99bce8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbourbon-whiskey-tariffs-europe-canada-trump-trade-war-prices-cost-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20American%20bourbon%20industry%20is%20going%20through%20a%20correction%20after%20a%202000s%20boom.%20Trump's%20trade%20war%20is%20making%20things%20even%20worse.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbourbon-whiskey-tariffs-europe-canada-trump-trade-wa